description.plain:
Bankrol Hayden, real name Hayden Inacio, is a rapper from Modesto, California, who was born on September 30, 2001.

In 2018, Hayden was in a serious car crash, for which he spent twenty days in a hospital and six days on life support. He reflected on the incident in his May 2018 track “29,” giving him a significant boost in attention.

Hayden is best known for his Luh Kel-assisted song “Brothers,” which racked up more than twenty-two million views on YouTube as of June 2021.

On June 26, 2020, Bankrol Hayden released his debut album, Pain Is Temporary, lead by its set of commercially successful singles—“Brothers,” “Costa Rica” and its The Kid LAROI-assisted remix, and “Rich Bitch.” The project debuted at #197 on the Billboard 200, thanks in part to features from Luh Kel, The Kid LAROI, Polo G and Lil Baby.

description.plain:
On “Brothers,“ Bankrol Hayden recruits Luh Kel for an upbeat track. The two artists express their love and appreciation for their “brothers”. Due to the two consistently struggling with heartbreaks, they begin to realize their brothers are all they can count on.

Hayden teased the track multiple times prior to its release on his Twitter, as early as seven months prior up until a few weeks before.

description.plain: On “29,” Bankrol Hayden reflects on the car crash he was involved in on November 29, 2017. The crash occurred in Modesto, California and there were two fatalities resulting from it. The song highlights the hardships of surviving something so traumatic.

songs.title: Costa Rica (Remix)

description.plain: Bankrol Hayden enlists The Kid LAROI. for the remix of his January 2020 single, “Costa Rica.” Notably, at the time of the remix’s releases, Bankrol and Laroi are 18 and 16 years of age respectively. The money-driven song is identical to the original, with the exception of Bankrol’s second verse being replaced with Laroi’s.
